## Latest Updates - December 2024

### ✅ **Local Configuration & Multiple Endpoints Support - COMPLETED**

#### **New Features Implemented:**
- **🏠 Local LLM Support:** Complete support for local LLM models (Ollama, LM Studio, etc.)
- **🔗 Multiple Endpoints:** Support for multiple additional endpoints per agent
- **💾 Data Persistence:** Proper saving and loading of local configuration data
- **🖥️ UI Enhancement:** Modern interface for managing local endpoints

#### **Technical Implementation:**

##### **Backend Changes:**
```python
# Enhanced LocalModelConfig with additional endpoints
class LocalEndpoint(PydanticBaseModel):
    name: str = Field(..., description="Endpoint name")
    host: str = Field(..., description="Endpoint host") 
    port: int = Field(..., description="Endpoint port")
    endpoint: str = Field(..., description="Endpoint path")
    model: str = Field(..., description="Model name for this endpoint")
    is_active: bool = Field(default=True, description="Whether endpoint is active")

class LocalModelConfig(PydanticBaseModel):
    host: str = Field(default="localhost", description="Local model host")
    port: int = Field(default=8080, description="Local model port")
    endpoint: str = Field(default="/api/chat", description="Local model endpoint")
    model_name: str = Field(..., description="Local model name")
    additional_endpoints: Optional[List[LocalEndpoint]] = Field(default=[], description="Additional endpoints")
```

##### **Frontend Changes:**
```typescript
// Enhanced AgentData interface with additional endpoints
interface AgentData {
  // ... existing fields
  is_local_model?: boolean;
  local_config?: {
    host: string;
    port: number;
    endpoint: string;
    model_name?: string;
  };
  additional_endpoints?: {
    name: string;
    host: string;
    port: number;
    endpoint: string;
    model: string;
    is_active: boolean;
  }[];
}
```

#### **Ollama Integration Standards:**

##### **Recommended Ollama Configuration:**
```javascript
// Primary Endpoint (Chat Completions - OpenAI Compatible)
{
  host: "localhost",
  port: 11434,
  endpoint: "/v1/chat/completions",
  model: "llama2"
}

// Additional Endpoints Examples
[
  {
    name: "Mistral Endpoint",
    host: "localhost", 
    port: 11434,
    endpoint: "/v1/chat/completions",
    model: "mistral",
    is_active: true
  },
  {
    name: "Code Llama",
    host: "localhost",
    port: 11434, 
    endpoint: "/v1/chat/completions",
    model: "codellama",
    is_active: true
  }
]
```

##### **Supported Ollama Models:**
- **🟢 Beginner:** llama2:7b, mistral:7b, orca-mini (4GB RAM)
- **🟡 Intermediate:** llama2:13b, codellama:13b (8GB RAM)
- **🔴 Advanced:** llama2:70b, mixtral:8x7b (32GB+ RAM)

#### **Data Flow Standards:**

##### **Create/Update Agent Flow:**
1. **Frontend:** AgentBuilder collects local configuration and additional endpoints
2. **Data Transformation:** Convert UI data to API format with additional_endpoints array
3. **Backend:** AgentService saves complete local_config with additional_endpoints
4. **Database:** Store as JSON in local_config column
5. **Response:** Return success with agent_id

##### **Load Agent for Edit Flow:**
1. **Frontend:** Request agent data from API
2. **Backend:** Return complete agent data including local_config.additional_endpoints
3. **Data Transformation:** Convert API data to UI format with separate additional_endpoints array
4. **UI Rendering:** Display primary endpoint and additional endpoints list
5. **User Interaction:** Allow add/edit/delete additional endpoints

#### **MANDATORY Implementation Rules:**

##### **Backend Rules:**
- ✅ All local configuration must support additional_endpoints array
- ✅ AgentService must handle LocalModelConfig with additional endpoints
- ✅ Database JSON column must store complete endpoint configuration
- ✅ API responses must include all endpoint data
- ✅ Validation must check endpoint format and accessibility

##### **Frontend Rules:**
- ✅ AgentBuilder must load existing additional endpoints when editing
- ✅ UI must allow adding unlimited additional endpoints
- ✅ Data must be properly transformed between UI and API formats
- ✅ Local configuration must be clearly separated from online configuration
- ✅ Endpoint validation must be performed before saving

##### **Authentication Fix:**
- ✅ Optional authentication for agent update endpoints
- ✅ Graceful handling of authentication failures
- ✅ Proper token validation and error handling

#### **Performance Standards:**
- **Local Endpoint Response Time:** < 500ms for localhost connections
- **Multiple Endpoints:** Support up to 10 additional endpoints per agent
- **Data Persistence:** 100% reliability for saving/loading configurations
- **UI Responsiveness:** Instant add/remove endpoint operations

#### **Testing Requirements:**
- ✅ Backend unit tests for LocalModelConfig and additional endpoints
- ✅ Frontend integration tests for AgentBuilder local configuration
- ✅ End-to-end tests for complete create/edit/save workflow
- ✅ Ollama integration testing with real local models

